{
  "stem": "8947.4",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then they were paid for our labors, you know?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't get an-- we were the slave laborers for these construction companies, you know?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I was in Bremen through the whole winter and fall of 1944.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we-- by end of March, they took us from Bremen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because I think they-- they-- we didn't look any more good for work.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were weakened, really.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then we had to march on foot for 30 kilometers.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I tell you, I call that a death march.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Many of us didn't make it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Some were shot.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Others collapsed.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I could tell you a lot about this death march.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then, finally, some of us who arrived arrived to Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, see, the death march-- we were, first of all, poorly clad.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and our guards were very nicely dressed up with boots, you know?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we-- we had-- I remember that during the death march, we had a stop.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we-- that sticks into my memory.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was like a hut of some sort.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were locked in there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were not allowed to get out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And if we had-- if we had to toilet is we had to make it there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I remember, you know, we-- we didn't get any utensils.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we had a kind of a-- you know, like the soldiers have a metal thing and you can drink your soup from there.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And-- and we had to use that for other purpose.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then we heard-- there was a very bad SS woman, who was with us-- very-- one of the-- some of the worst, who would strip you in the middle of the winter, from-- if you had a rag around you, because you work faster if you are cold.",
      "word_count": 49
    }
  ],
